content:
A dashboard displays data from each widget's source report. You can control which data is visible based on the running user.

A dashboard viewer sees data based on the assigned privileges and access of the dashboard's running user. A static dashboard displays data using the configured user's privileges. A dynamic dashboard displays data based on the logged-in user.

To specify which data to display in a dashboard, select a running user. You can change the running user to control which data is visible to viewers.

A dynamic dashboard shows each user only the data that they have access to.
title: Controlling Salesforce Dashboard Data Visibility
